62
00:04:11,505 --> 00:04:16,667
Every time, enough time passes and the player will eventually cross the magic threshold

63
00:04:16,727 --> 00:04:18,887
that tells the game that it should return a failed state.

64
00:04:19,547 --> 00:04:24,509
So there's an interrupt, the game resets itself, and the player respawns.

65
00:04:25,529 --> 00:04:29,450
Now what's interesting about that is that big orange dot

66
00:04:30,467 --> 00:04:33,749
that you see over there on the far left, sits outside of that state space.

67
00:04:34,710 --> 00:04:35,391
Why is that interesting?

68
00:04:35,411 --> 00:04:40,774
Well, because what it means is that ultimately the cost of failure is external to the game.

69
00:04:41,355 --> 00:04:41,955
Think about that.

70
00:04:42,849 --> 00:04:48,273
I'm going to be willing to bet that most of the people in this room put some kind of premium on the consistency of the player experience.

71
00:04:48,993 --> 00:04:54,617
