72
00:04:54,978 --> 00:04:57,920
incurs a cost that can't possibly be measured.

73
00:04:58,340 --> 00:05:03,363
Because the value of a person's time is completely dependent on who they are and the kind of life that they live.

74
00:05:04,804 --> 00:05:05,385
It depends on...

75
00:05:07,355 --> 00:05:10,681
a number of things but it's safe to say that even if they're playing the same game

76
00:05:10,902 --> 00:05:13,246
that the cost for this guy is going to be different from the cost

77
00:05:13,667 --> 00:05:14,128
for this guy.

78
00:05:17,028 --> 00:05:17,969
But that's what we have right now.

79
00:05:18,730 --> 00:05:20,411
And implicit in that is a kind of bargain

80
00:05:20,571 --> 00:05:22,712
that exists between the player and the game, right?

81
00:05:23,092 --> 00:05:25,234
Which says that in return for submitting themselves

82
00:05:25,574 --> 00:05:26,895
to this binary failure model,

83
00:05:27,255 --> 00:05:31,198
players have an expectation that they can evaluate

84
00:05:31,518 --> 00:05:33,679
the risks associated with the actions

85
00:05:33,699 --> 00:05:34,560
that they're about to take.

