00:11:51,743 --> 00:11:55,067
to going through a reversal in the kind of traditional narrative sense.

192
00:11:55,768 --> 00:11:59,813
It yields that water cooler anecdote moment that's completely the player's own.

193
00:12:00,333 --> 00:12:00,894
So there I was.

194
00:12:03,682 --> 00:12:08,705
But dynamically what it means is that the system defined by the player and the game

195
00:12:08,925 --> 00:12:14,548
interacting at runtime is able to absorb serious shocks and recover without interruption.

196
00:12:15,368 --> 00:12:18,870
It's resilient in the way that economists typically use the term.

197
00:12:19,670 --> 00:12:23,652
So what we want to do is we want to replace the failure cliff with something a little

198
00:12:23,692 --> 00:12:25,413
softer and a little more reversible.

199
00:12:26,353 --> 00:12:28,815
Something that follows a bit more of the kind of stimulus response curve.

200
00:12:30,577 --> 00:12:34,799
And that kind of behavior emerges from having a feedback system that prevents the player

201
00:12:35,439 --> 00:12:40,122
from progressing unimpeded into meaningless degenerate end state, while at the same time

202
00:12:40,282 --> 00:12:45,625
plucking them out of that, kicking them back into a more volatile game condition in which

203
00:12:45,685 --> 00:12:50,068
success is by no means ensured, but without driving them to the point where they rage

